<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,654,2011]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,654,679]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males are easily distinguished from two most similar known relatives (
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Gonzalez-Sponga" authorityYear="1998" box="[1120,1388,654,679]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudoblechroscelis">
<emphasis box="[1120,1388,654,679]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. pseudoblechroscelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acrensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. acrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by male pedipalp (procursus with distinctively shaped distal element; bulbal process with ventral sclerotized area and bifid dorso-distal flap; 
<figureCitation box="[655,787,726,751]" captionStart="FIGURES13–17" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1836,1858]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,373,1807]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,373,1815]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES13–17.Mesabolivar acrensissp. n.(13–15, ZFMK Ar 18942)and M.maraba sp. n. (16–17,ZFMK Ar18948).13– 14. Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views. 15–16. Left bulbal processes, prolateral views (arrow points at distinctive sclerotized area). 17. Left procursus, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: b, genital bulb; bp, bulbal process; c, coxa; f, femur; p, procursus, ta, tarsus; ti, tibia; tr, trochanter.Scale lines:0.5 (13–14, 17), 0.3 (15–16)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202523/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Figs 16–17</figureCitation>
); from most species (except 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Gonzalez-Sponga" authorityYear="1998" box="[1122,1389,726,751]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudoblechroscelis">
<emphasis box="[1122,1389,726,751]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. pseudoblechroscelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acrensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. acrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2000" box="[257,403,762,787]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huambisa">
<emphasis box="[257,403,762,787]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. huambisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) also by armature of male chelicerae (identical in shape to those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[1160,1289,764,787]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acrensis">
<emphasis box="[1160,1289,764,787]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. acrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, cf. 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES18–25" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1556,1578]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,195,1532]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,193,1535]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES18–25. Mesabolivar acrensissp.n. (18–22; ZFMK Ar 18942–43) andM.maraba sp. n.(23–25, ZFMK Ar 18948). 18–19. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. 20–21, 23–24. Epigyna, ventral and lateral views. 22, 25. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal views.Abbreviations:ep, epigynal pocket; pp, pore plate; v, ‘valve’. Scale lines:0.5." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202525/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Figs 18– 19</figureCitation>
; pair of slender apophyses, straight in lateral view), and by shape of epigynum (
<figureCitation box="[1137,1272,798,823]" captionStart="FIGURES18–25" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1556,1578]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,195,1532]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,193,1535]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES18–25. Mesabolivar acrensissp.n. (18–22; ZFMK Ar 18942–43) andM.maraba sp. n.(23–25, ZFMK Ar 18948). 18–19. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. 20–21, 23–24. Epigyna, ventral and lateral views. 22, 25. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal views.Abbreviations:ep, epigynal pocket; pp, pore plate; v, ‘valve’. Scale lines:0.5." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202525/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Figs 23–24</figureCitation>
; large median depression, lateral margins slightly diverging towards anterior, bordered posteriorly by large pocket; pair of conical lateral processes directed slightly towards posterior - epigynum possibly indistinguishable from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[1224,1353,871,894]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acrensis">
<emphasis box="[1224,1353,871,894]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. acrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, due to variation, see description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[485,618,908,931]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acrensis">
<emphasis box="[485,618,908,931]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. acrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
above); from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[790,923,908,931]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acrensis">
<emphasis box="[790,923,908,931]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. acrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other putatively close relatives also by female internal genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[458,551,942,967]" captionStart="FIGURES18–25" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1556,1578]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,195,1532]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,193,1535]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES18–25. Mesabolivar acrensissp.n. (18–22; ZFMK Ar 18942–43) andM.maraba sp. n.(23–25, ZFMK Ar 18948). 18–19. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. 20–21, 23–24. Epigyna, ventral and lateral views. 22, 25. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal views.Abbreviations:ep, epigynal pocket; pp, pore plate; v, ‘valve’. Scale lines:0.5." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202525/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Figs 25</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[570,601,943,967]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–47" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1829,1851]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1808]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,193,1808]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 32–47. Female epigyna in ventral and lateral views and cleared female genitalia, dorsal views, Mesabolivar pseudoblechroscelisgroup (part 1). 32–38. M. acrensissp. n., from Rio Branco (32–33, 38, ZFMK Ar 18943), Cruzeirodo Sul (34–37, ZFMK Ar 18946). 39–41. M. maraba sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 18948). 42–47. M. huambisa Huber, 2000, from Samiria (42– 43, MUSM), Tabatinga (44–45, ZFMK Ar 18950), and Belém (46–47, ZFMK Ar 18951)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202529/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">39</figureCitation>
; elongated pore-plates in transversal position, wider apart than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2000" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huambisa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. huambisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (female of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Gonzalez-Sponga" authorityYear="1998" box="[399,662,978,1003]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudoblechroscelis">
<emphasis box="[399,662,978,1003]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. pseudoblechroscelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
unknown).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
