<subSubSection lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,654,2011]" box="[199,536,1266,1291]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,412,1266,1291]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Description. Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[427,528,1266,1291]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">holotype</typeStatus>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,654,2011]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">MEASUREMENTS. Total body length 2.7, carapace width 1.2. Distance PME-PME 140 µm, diameter PME 120 µm, distance PME-ALE 90 µm, distance AME-AME 55 µm, diameter AME 55 µm. Sternum width/length: 0.95/ 0.60. Leg 1: 36.2 (8.8 + 0.5 + 8.8 + 16.1 + 2.0), tibia 2: 6.1, tibia 3: 4.4, tibia 4: 6.3; tibia 1 L/d: 80. Femora 1–4 width (at half length): 0.15, 0.17, 0.20, 0.18.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,654,2011]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<collectionCode box="[199,278,1447,1471]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">COLOR</collectionCode>
(in ethanol). Carapace ochre-yellow, with large brown median mark, ocular area also darkened posteriorly laterally; sternum orange; legs ochre, with indistinct darker rings on femora (subdistally) and tibiae (proximally; subdistal rings barely visible), tips of femora and tibiae whitish; abdomen greenish, with dark internal marks dorsally and laterally, without ventral mark.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,654,2011]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<collectionCode box="[199,264,1591,1614]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">BODY</collectionCode>
. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation box="[445,516,1590,1615]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1532,1554]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1511]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1511]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Live specimens, Mesabolivar pseudoblechroscelis group. 1–2. M. acrensis sp. n., male and female from Rio Branco. 3–4. M. maraba sp. n., male and female from Marabá. 5–6. M. huambisa Huber, 2000, male from Tabatinga, female from Belém.7–8.M.amazonicus sp. n., male and female from Humaitá.9–10.M.jamari sp. n., male and female from Jamari. 11–12. M.tapajos sp. n., male and female from Tapajós." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202521/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
; ocular area raised (higher than usual in genus); carapace with distinct median furrow; clypeus slightly swollen, with sclerotized margin; sternum unmodified.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,654,2011]" box="[199,1124,1662,1687]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
CHELICERAE. Identical in shape to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[589,719,1663,1686]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acrensis">
<emphasis box="[589,719,1663,1686]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. acrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(cf. 
<figureCitation box="[771,899,1662,1687]" captionStart="FIGURES18–25" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1556,1578]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,195,1532]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,193,1535]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES18–25. Mesabolivar acrensissp.n. (18–22; ZFMK Ar 18942–43) andM.maraba sp. n.(23–25, ZFMK Ar 18948). 18–19. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. 20–21, 23–24. Epigyna, ventral and lateral views. 22, 25. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal views.Abbreviations:ep, epigynal pocket; pp, pore plate; v, ‘valve’. Scale lines:0.5." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202525/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Figs 18–19</figureCitation>
), but slightly larger.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,654,2011]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<collectionCode box="[199,268,1699,1722]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">PALPS</collectionCode>
. In general as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[470,601,1700,1723]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acrensis">
<emphasis box="[470,601,1700,1723]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. acrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(cf. 
<figureCitation box="[657,787,1698,1723]" captionStart="FIGURES13–17" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1836,1858]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,373,1807]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,373,1815]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES13–17.Mesabolivar acrensissp. n.(13–15, ZFMK Ar 18942)and M.maraba sp. n. (16–17,ZFMK Ar18948).13– 14. Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views. 15–16. Left bulbal processes, prolateral views (arrow points at distinctive sclerotized area). 17. Left procursus, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: b, genital bulb; bp, bulbal process; c, coxa; f, femur; p, procursus, ta, tarsus; ti, tibia; tr, trochanter.Scale lines:0.5 (13–14, 17), 0.3 (15–16)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202523/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Figs 13–14</figureCitation>
), but larger (e.g., femur length: 1.14 vs. 0.86); procursus distally clearly different from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[495,626,1735,1758]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acrensis">
<emphasis box="[495,626,1735,1758]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. acrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[643,729,1734,1759]" captionStart="FIGURES13–17" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1836,1858]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,373,1807]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,373,1815]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES13–17.Mesabolivar acrensissp. n.(13–15, ZFMK Ar 18942)and M.maraba sp. n. (16–17,ZFMK Ar18948).13– 14. Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views. 15–16. Left bulbal processes, prolateral views (arrow points at distinctive sclerotized area). 17. Left procursus, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: b, genital bulb; bp, bulbal process; c, coxa; f, femur; p, procursus, ta, tarsus; ti, tibia; tr, trochanter.Scale lines:0.5 (13–14, 17), 0.3 (15–16)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202523/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
); bulbal process with ventral sclerotized area and bifid dorsodistal flap (
<figureCitation box="[277,361,1770,1795]" captionStart="FIGURES13–17" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1836,1858]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,373,1807]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,373,1815]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES13–17.Mesabolivar acrensissp. n.(13–15, ZFMK Ar 18942)and M.maraba sp. n. (16–17,ZFMK Ar18948).13– 14. Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views. 15–16. Left bulbal processes, prolateral views (arrow points at distinctive sclerotized area). 17. Left procursus, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: b, genital bulb; bp, bulbal process; c, coxa; f, femur; p, procursus, ta, tarsus; ti, tibia; tr, trochanter.Scale lines:0.5 (13–14, 17), 0.3 (15–16)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202523/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,654,2011]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<collectionCode box="[199,258,1807,1830]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">LEGS</collectionCode>
. Without spines and curved hairs, few vertical hairs; retrolateral trichobothrium on tibia 1 at 2.5%; prolateral trichobothrium present on tibia 1; tarsus 1 with ~25 pseudosegments, distally fairly distinct.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,654,2011]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,1878,1903]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Male</emphasis>
(variation). Some males with indistinct dark mark behind gonopore. Tibia 
<quantity box="[1093,1135,1878,1903]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
five other males from 
<typeStatus box="[1388,1436,1879,1903]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">type</typeStatus>
locality: 7.1–10.2 (mean 8.7). The single male from 
<collectingRegion box="[755,836,1915,1939]" country="Brazil" name="Amapa" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Amapá</collectingRegion>
has a slightly different procursus tip (slightly larger relative to base of procursus) and is therefore assigned tentatively (cf. female below). Tibia 
<quantity box="[1178,1221,1950,1975]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
this male: 9.6.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,654,2011]" lastBlockId="16.[151,1437,151,789]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,1986,2011]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Female.</emphasis>
In general similar to male but carapace ochre-brown rather than yellow to orange, with larger brown median mark; ocular area slightly lower than in males; dark rings and whitish tips of femora and tibiae more distinct; clypeus less swollen and margin not sclerotized. Tibia 
<quantity box="[895,942,188,213]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
seven females from 
<typeStatus box="[1190,1238,189,213]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">type</typeStatus>
locality: 4.1–5.5 (mean 4.7). Epigynum as in 
<figureCitation box="[506,639,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES18–25" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1556,1578]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,195,1532]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,193,1535]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES18–25. Mesabolivar acrensissp.n. (18–22; ZFMK Ar 18942–43) andM.maraba sp. n.(23–25, ZFMK Ar 18948). 18–19. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. 20–21, 23–24. Epigyna, ventral and lateral views. 22, 25. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal views.Abbreviations:ep, epigynal pocket; pp, pore plate; v, ‘valve’. Scale lines:0.5." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202525/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Figs 23–24</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[709,782,224,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–47" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1829,1851]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1808]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,193,1808]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 32–47. Female epigyna in ventral and lateral views and cleared female genitalia, dorsal views, Mesabolivar pseudoblechroscelisgroup (part 1). 32–38. M. acrensissp. n., from Rio Branco (32–33, 38, ZFMK Ar 18943), Cruzeirodo Sul (34–37, ZFMK Ar 18946). 39–41. M. maraba sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 18948). 42–47. M. huambisa Huber, 2000, from Samiria (42– 43, MUSM), Tabatinga (44–45, ZFMK Ar 18950), and Belém (46–47, ZFMK Ar 18951)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202529/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">40–41</figureCitation>
; anterior plate with large median depression bordered posteriorly by large pocket; pair of conical lateral processes directed slightly towards posterior; posterior plate large, simple. Internal genitalia as in 
<figureCitation box="[574,662,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES18–25" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1556,1578]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,195,1532]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,193,1535]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES18–25. Mesabolivar acrensissp.n. (18–22; ZFMK Ar 18942–43) andM.maraba sp. n.(23–25, ZFMK Ar 18948). 18–19. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. 20–21, 23–24. Epigyna, ventral and lateral views. 22, 25. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal views.Abbreviations:ep, epigynal pocket; pp, pore plate; v, ‘valve’. Scale lines:0.5." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202525/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Figs 25</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[674,704,296,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–47" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1829,1851]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1808]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,193,1808]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 32–47. Female epigyna in ventral and lateral views and cleared female genitalia, dorsal views, Mesabolivar pseudoblechroscelisgroup (part 1). 32–38. M. acrensissp. n., from Rio Branco (32–33, 38, ZFMK Ar 18943), Cruzeirodo Sul (34–37, ZFMK Ar 18946). 39–41. M. maraba sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 18948). 42–47. M. huambisa Huber, 2000, from Samiria (42– 43, MUSM), Tabatinga (44–45, ZFMK Ar 18950), and Belém (46–47, ZFMK Ar 18951)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202529/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">39</figureCitation>
, with elongated pore-plates in transversal position and far apart, and distinctive median dark anterior structure.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
In the three females from 
<collectingRegion box="[503,587,368,392]" country="Brazil" name="Amapa" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Amapá</collectingRegion>
, the margins of the median depression are approximately parallel and the conical lateral processes are slightly shorter; they are therefore assigned tentatively (cf. male above). tibia 
<quantity box="[1344,1387,404,429]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
two females: 5.7 (both; legs 1 missing in third female).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,388,476,501]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Natural history.</emphasis>
At Marabá, the spiders were mostly found under large palm leaves on the ground. In Macapá, they occupied small cavities in the ground and the spaces under the exposed roots of trees.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,548,573]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known from 
<typeStatus box="[517,565,549,573]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">type</typeStatus>
locality in 
<collectingRegion box="[699,749,548,572]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Pará</collectingRegion>
state and from specimens assigned tentatively from 
<collectingRegion box="[1355,1436,548,572]" country="Brazil" name="Amapa" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Amapá</collectingRegion>
state (
<collectingCountry box="[217,289,583,608]" name="Brazil" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Brazil</collectingCountry>
) (
<figureCitation box="[311,411,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURES 722–723" captionStartId="162.[151,264,1872,1894]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1850]" captionTargetId="figure@162.[151,1436,193,1850]" captionTargetPageId="162" captionText="FIGURES 722–723. Known distribution of the Mesabolivar pseudoblechroscelis group. For the dubious type locality of M. exlineae, see under description of M.jamari. TL, type locality." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202697/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 722</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,620,645]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Note.</emphasis>
The illustrations in 
<bibRefCitation box="[491,676,620,645]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refId="ref100191" refString="Machado, E. O. (2011) Estratificacao de habitat, diversidade e evolucao do genero Mesabolivar Gonzalez-Sponga, 1998 (Araneae: Pholcidae). PhD thesis, University of Sao Paulo, 162 pp." type="book">Machado (2011)</bibRefCitation>
of species “sp. 07” strongly remind of the present species. It is not clear which specimens were used for the illustrations: the 
<typeStatus box="[823,882,656,680]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">types</typeStatus>
from Rio Branco (
<collectingRegion box="[1104,1162,656,680]" country="Brazil" name="Acre" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Acre</collectingRegion>
) or the specimens from Floresta Nacional de Caxiuanã, Melgaço (
<collectingRegion box="[621,677,692,716]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Pará</collectingRegion>
). The latter locality is approximately between and fairly close to the localities listed above (
<quantity box="[414,502,727,752]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.85" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="km" value="485.0">485 km</quantity>
from the 
<typeStatus box="[617,665,728,752]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">type</typeStatus>
locality Marabá, 
<quantity box="[868,955,727,752]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="km" value="190.0">190 km</quantity>
from Macapá), while Rio Branco is more than 
<quantity box="[206,305,764,789]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="km" value="2100.0">2100 km</quantity>
west and much less likely to have the same species.
</paragraph>
